<TEXT>Your browser is unsupported We recommend using the latest version of IE11, Edge, Chrome, Firefox or Safari. University of Illinois Chicago Search the site University of Illinois Chicago Computer Science Main Menu Expand Undergraduate menu Expand Graduate menu Expand Research menu Expand Faculty and Staff menu Expand News menu Expand Events menu Eyebrow menu Break Through Tech Give Alumni UIC Engineering Home UIC menu UIC.edu Campus Map Search College of Engineering Riazi brings big data experience to department Andrea Poet | Posted on October 11, 2022 Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link Sara Riazi This semester, Riazi is teaching two sections of CS 141, Program Design II. “UIC is a great public school and seeing how the educators here care about the students is amazing,” Riazi said. “I enjoy being a member of such a wonderful community.” Most recently, Riazi served as a visiting assistant professor at the University of North Carolina at Charlotte. Prior to that, she worked as an assistant professor at the University of New Haven, Connecticut, and was a graduate research fellow at the University of Oregon. She also worked as a software engineer for a web design, ecommerce consulting, and digital marketing firm in Tehran, Iran. Riazi received her bachelor’s degree in software engineering from Shahid Beheshti University, Tehran, and her master’s degree and her PhD in computer science from the University of Oregon. “My focus is big data and data science, and I want to prepare our students in this area to be able to continue their career in this competitive field,” Riazi said. Modified on October 11, 2022 Footer Menu Undergraduate Resources Graduate Resources Faculty Resources ABET Accreditation Social Media Accounts xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Linked In xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Twitter xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Instagram xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? YouTube Contact For CS student and facult